Amphibious Endurance	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES																		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Water Breathing],[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Aquatic]				DESC:Water-breathing creatures can survive out of water for two hours per point of contitution, after which the effects of suffocation begins.																	SOURCEPAGE:Shb	
Armor Proficiency (Aquatic)	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES																						DESC:Normally, a surface dwelling characther is not proficient in any type of aquatic armor (see equipment pag 24). However, taking this feat allows the character to be proficient in any type of aquatic armor for which he has a corresponding proficiency. In other words, if the character is proficient with light and medium armor, taking this feat allows him to use light aquatic and medium aquatic armor normally. This feat needs to be taken only once, regardless of how many types of armor the character is proficient with. This feat applies only to surface dwellers.				ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.ArmorProfAquaticLight|PREPROFWITHARMOR:1,TYPE.Light	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.ArmorProfAquaticMedium|PREPROFWITHARMOR:1,TYPE.Medium	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE.ArmorProfAquaticHeavy|PREPROFWITHARMOR:1,TYPE.Heavy											SOURCEPAGE:Shb
Barroom Brawler	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Toughness									PRESTAT:1,CON=13									DESC:You gain +4 hit points for the purposes of defending against subdual damage. In addition, your unarmed attacks do 1d4 points of subdual damage plus your strength modifies (1d3 for small creatures).																	SOURCEPAGE:Shb	UDAM:1,1,1d2,1d3,1d4,1d6,1d8,1d10,1d12,2d8
Cast Iron Stomach	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES													PRESTAT:1,CON=13									DESC:You derive nourishment from spoiled food and can avoid dehydration by drinking seawater with few ill effects. By substituting on these unusual provisions, you double the amount of time you can go without fresh food and water.																	SOURCEPAGE:Shb	
Child of the Sea	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES			PRELEVELMAX:1																			DESC:At some point in the near or distant past, you had an ancestor who was a member of an aquatic species. This gives you a greater ability to hold your breath. For every five point of constitution, you may hold your breath for one hour before having to surface for air.																	SOURCEPAGE:Shb	
Create Manikin	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:ItemCreation	VISIBLE:YES			PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=12																			DESC:A manikin serves as a focus for the transmission of spells against a target not currently within the spell's range.																	SOURCEPAGE:Shb	
Endurance Swimmer	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	VISIBLE:YES				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Endurance									PRESTAT:1,STR=13									DESC:You suffer a -1 penalty on swim checks for every 20 pounds of armor and equipment you carry, up to your maximum load.																	SOURCEPAGE:Shb	
